We Movie Project

Requirements
Before starting, ensure you have the following installed:

PHP >= 8.1
Composer
Node.js & npm
Symfony CLI (optional but recommended)

##Installation Steps

1. Clone the repository
First, clone the repository to your local machine:

git clone https://github.com/nour1808/we-movies.git
cd we-movie

2. Install PHP Dependencies
Install the necessary PHP dependencies using Composer:
composer install

3. Create .env.local File
Copy the default environment configuration file .env to .env.local:

cp .env .env.local
Edit .env.local to configure your database and API keys:

API_URL="https://api.themoviedb.org/3"
API_KEY="your_api_key"

4. Install Node.js Dependencies
Use npm to install the required JavaScript dependencies:
npm install

5. Build Assets
After installing the dependencies, build the assets with:
npm run dev

Use npm run build for production builds.

6. Run the Symfony Server
   You can start the Symfony server with:

symfony server:start

7. Access the Application
http://127.0.0.1:8000


